column1: 2009-2010 Iowa Public School and AEA Teacher Information
Source: Iowa Department of Education, Bureau of Planning, Research, Development, and Evaluation, Basic Educational Data Survey, Staff File.

column2: Figures represent average total salaries for staff by position. Some staff (5,002 teachers) may be reported in multiple positions.
For example, a teacher may also be employed as a principal or superintendent.  The average, minimum, and maximum salaries include these staff.
Teacher salary calculations were based upon total salaries for full-time public school staff with contract days>=180 and base salary>=$28,000.
Other teachers are teachers with a full-time contract, but contract days are<180 or base salary<$28,000.
Data under 'FT Teachers with Teaching Position Codes Only' was calculated including only teachers with teaching position codes.
Regular salary is the portion of salary that is paid for direct position responsibilities, including teacher compensation, phase and professional development.
Base salary includes all that is in regular salary except professional development.
Total salary includes regular salary and extra salary paid for extra curriculur and extra duties.
